AOPet — third-party assets and licenses
========================================

Sprite art
----------

The cat sprite frames bundled under
`Sources/AOPet/Resources/sprites/oneko/` are derived from the Oneko cat
sprite atlas distributed by adryd325/oneko.js.

  Source repo:  https://github.com/adryd325/oneko.js
  Source file:  oneko.gif (256x128 atlas, 8x4 grid of 32x32 frames)
  License:      MIT

Original artwork: Oneko (Naoshi Ikeya, 1989).

The atlas is fetched at build-asset-generation time by
`scripts/generate_sprites.py`, cropped per the canonical oneko.js
`spriteSets` table, and saved as per-mood PNG frames. No transformations
beyond cropping are applied.

The full text of the oneko.js MIT license follows. A copy is preserved
here so distributing AOPet does not require pulling adryd325/oneko.js as
a build dependency.

